on is characterized by a range of psychiatric symptoms that are secondary to the primary physical illness. Management of these mental disorders typically occurs within general hospital settings, where both the physical and mental health aspects of the patient can be addressed concurrently. This condition underscores the intricate connection between physical health and mental well-being, highlighting the importance of a holistic approach to treatment.\",7\r\n462,躯体感染所致精神障碍,\"\"\"躯体感染所致精神障碍\"\"是一种由身体感染引发的精神障碍。这种精神障碍是由病毒、细菌、螺旋体、真菌、原虫等病原体引起的脑外全身性感染所导致的。具体而言，当这些病原体感染身体并引发全身性感染时，可能会对大脑功能产生影响，进而导致精神障碍的出现。因此，\"\"躯体感染所致精神障碍\"\"强调了感染与精神健康之间的直接关联，表明全身性感染是此类精神障碍的根本原因。\",2\r\n1340,LIPOWSKI,Lipowski is a researcher who proposed the theory that the common pathophysiological change in mental disorders due to physical diseases is a diffuse brain energy alteration,2\r\n450,AMERICAN PSYCHIATRIC ASSOCIATION,\"The American Psychiatric Association is the organization that developed the DSM system for diagnosing mental disorders, including the introduction of the multi-axial diagnostic principle in DSM-III in 1980>\",2\r\n210,FINK,\"Fink found that 5% of 392 internal medicine inpatients had somatization disorder under ICD-10 criteria, while only 1.5% under DSM-IV criteria\",3\r\n211,MDE WAAL,Mde Waal reported a prevalence of 16.1% for undifferentiated somatoform disorder,1\r\n1720,GANZER SYNDROME,\"A psychological condition characterized by approximate answers, twilight state, and post-event amnesia, often occurring in prisoners with significant psychological trauma, classified under dissociative disorders in ICD-10 and CCMD2-R in China. It typically resolves naturally within days or weeks without special treatment, though electroconvulsive therapy and sedatives have been used historically. Follow-up is essential for recovery.\",3\r\n1721,GANZER,\"The researcher who reported cases of a peculiar twilight state in patients, leading to the identification of Ganser syndrome, a condition marke